			<div change="#StB" n="41" type="r">
				<sp who="#V.">
					<p><pb facs="#f042"/><milestone facs="#f042_z000" n="41" unit="folio_number"/><lb/>However<add change="#StC" facs="#f042_z001" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> I do not wish to dwell any<lb/> further upon individual instances. Personal<lb/><milestone facs="#f042_z002" unit="guiding_line"/> <add change="#StBa" facs="#f042_z002" hand="#Wilde" place="above inline left margin" rend="caret_guiding_line">experience </add>is a most vicious and limited circle. <lb/>All that I desire to point out is<lb/> the general principle that <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">L</del><add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">l</add>ife imitates<lb/> <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">A</del><add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">a</add>rt far more than <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">A</del><add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">a</add>rt imitates <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">L</del><add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">l</add>ife,<lb/> and I feel sure that if you think<lb/> seriously about it you will find<lb/> that it is true. <del change="#StBa" facs="#f042_z003" hand="#Wilde" rend="multi-stroke">Art </del><add change="#StBa" facs="#f042_z004" hand="#Wilde" place="above" rend="no_caret"><del change="#StC" hand="#comp">L</del></add><add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">l</add><add change="#StBa" facs="#f042_z004" hand="#Wilde" place="above" rend="no_caret">ife</add> holds the mirror<lb/> up to <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">A</del><add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">a</add>rt, and either reproduces <del change="#StBa" facs="#f042_z005" hand="#Wilde" rend="multi-stroke">the </del>some<lb/> strange type <add change="#StBa" facs="#f042_z007" hand="#Wilde" place="above inline" rend="guiding_line">imagined by</add> <milestone facs="#f042_z007" unit="guiding_line"/><del change="#StBa" facs="#f042_z006" hand="#Wilde" rend="multi-stroke">of </del>painter or sculptor, or<lb/> realises in fact what has been<lb/> dreamed in fiction. Scientifically speaking,<lb/> the basis of <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">L</del><add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">l</add>ife<del change="#StC" facs="#f042_z008" hand="#comp">,</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f042_z009" hand="#comp" place="nc">--</add>the energy of <del change="#StC" facs="#f042_z010" hand="#comp">L</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f042_z010" hand="#comp" place="nc">l</add>ife<add change="#StC" facs="#f042_z010" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add><lb/> as Aristotle would call it<del change="#StC" facs="#f042_z009" hand="#comp">,</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f042_z009" hand="#comp" place="nc">--</add>is simply<lb/> the desire for expression, and <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">A</del><add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">a</add>rt is<lb/> always presenting various forms through<lb/> which <add change="#StBa" facs="#f042_z011" hand="#Wilde" place="above inline" rend="caret">this </add><milestone facs="#f042_z011" unit="caret"/>expression can be attained. <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">L</del><add change="#StC" hand="#comp" place="nc">l</add>ife <lb/>seizes on them and uses them<add change="#StC" facs="#f042_z012" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> even if <lb/>they be to her own hurt. Young men<lb/> have committed suicide because Rolla<lb/> did so, have<milestone n="intentions 32"/> died by their own hand<lb/> because by his own hand <del change="#StC" facs="#f042_z013">Rene </del><add change="#StC" facs="#f042_z013" place="nc">Werther </add>died.<lb/> Think of what we owe to the<lb/> imitation of Christ, of what we owe<lb/> to the imitation of CÃ¦sar. <lb/></p>
				</sp>
				<sp who="#C.">
					<p><hi change="#StB" hand="#Wilde" rend="underline">C</hi><del change="#StC" hand="#comp" rend="pencil"><hi change="#StB" hand="#Wilde" rend="underline">yril</hi></del>. The <del change="#StBa" facs="#f042_z014" hand="#Wilde" rend="single-stroke">point </del><add change="#StBa" facs="#f042_z015" hand="#Wilde" place="above" rend="no_caret">theory </add>is certainly a very <lb/>curious one<del change="#StBa" facs="#f042_z016" hand="#Wilde" rend="single-stroke"> and entirely new.</del><lb/><lb/><lb/></p>
